# Titel: Zoo


# **************************** Användargränsnitt ************************
When started the program should:
1. Ask the user for the date they want to come
2. Print what time the zoo is open that day
3. Ask the user at what time they wanna come/leave
4. Print out all the animals that are active at that time of the year and print out
   if any of those animals have feeding time in that time interval


# ************************** Minne / Datastruktur ************************
The animals are stored in a list with:
1. Names
2. Feeding-times
3. What time of the day the animals are awake
4. What time of the year the animals are active


# ***************************** Algoritm *********************************
The program imports the list of all the animals.
The program stores the input of the user as a month and a time.
The program prints out all the active animals and the ones that have feeding time by:
 1. checking if they are winter/summer active and compares with the stored value for month
 2. checking if the feeing time is in the intervall of the arrival/leaving time the user inputs



# ************************** Programskelett ******************************

     #**************************** Funktioner *********************************
     Function to check the date (special dates, wrong formats and so on), returns the month
     Function to check the time interval the user wants to visit, returns the arrival and leaving time
     Function to check the animals are active in the given month
     Function to check if any animals have feeding-time in the given time interval

     #*************** Klasser och dess metoder******************
     Class: classAnimal with name, awake_time, active_time and feeding_time
     Methods: get_name, get_awake_time, get_active_time, get_feeding_time


     #************ Huvudprogrammet ********************
Reads data from file and creates a list.
Compare with the user input.
Prints out different part of the list depending on the functions of comparing and the users inputs